sdale NY, away from his Rochester family."}],"cross_connections":[{"type":"parallel_careers","related_id":"HD6587","link_text":"Benjamin Munroe Burr","display_label":"a fellow Guaranty Trust executive and wartime veteran"}],"naming_inspiration":[{"name_element":"Kemp","inspired_by_id":"X01665","description":"Middle name carries his father George Kemp Ward's middle name forward to the next generation."}],"education":[],"career":[{"role":"Junior staff","organization":"Guaranty Trust Company of New York","location":"New York City","notes":"Early-career employment before WWI service."},{"role":"Partner","organization":"Hemphill, Noyes & Co.","location":"15 Broad Street, New York City","start_year":1919,"end_year":1939,"notes":"Joined the investment banking firm at 15 Broad Street upon return from France in 1919; remained partner until his 1939 death."}],"military_service":[{"war":"World War I","war_id":"WAR007","unit":"American Expeditionary Forces (France)","notes":"Served overseas in France during the First World War, after early career employment at Guaranty Trust Company of New York. Returned 1919 and joined Hemphill, Noyes & Co."}],"institutions":[],"landmarks":[],"artworks":[],"documents":[],"quotes":[],"statues":[],"slug":"kenneth-ward-1887"}},"burialCemetery":null,"institutionsById":{},"crossConnections":[]}